<item>
            <title>[LU-6027] Issues with EAs of orphan files and EAs with empty values</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6027</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Current b2_5 and master have the following issues with EAs:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Setting a new EA with an empty value, which is permitted according to attr(5), succeeds without actually storing the EA to the OSD.  A subsequent getxattr() call will return ENODATA.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Calling fgetxattr() on an orphan file may get ENOENT, if it causes an EA cache refill.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
                <environment></environment>
